22:38.457 --> 22:45.030 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Philippines also asked that
the tribunal
rule on the status of eight of
the features.

22:45.064 --> 22:51.403 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the tribunal ruled on most
of those and
importantly found none of the
features are

22:51.437 --> 23:00.446 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
full islands. So, none of them
get a 200-nautical-mile
exclusive economic zone. They
just get a 12-nautical-mile

23:00.479 --> 23:05.551 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
territorial sea if they're a
rock, and some
of them are underwater, and they
get no maritime

23:05.584 --> 23:06.685 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
entitlement whatsoever.

23:06.719 --> 23:08.420 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(CROSSTALK)

23:08.454 --> 23:11.390 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, let me just
stop you
there. What was China arguing
was the basis

23:11.423 --> 23:13.792 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
for its territorial claim, then?

23:13.826 --> 23:20.199 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BONNIE GLASER: Well, China has
argued, as
has five other claimants, that
they own many

23:20.232 --> 23:25.304 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of the islands. Some of them,
like China and
Taiwan, claim all of the islands
in the South

23:25.337 --> 23:27.239 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
China Sea.

23:27.273 --> 23:31.010 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This particular set of islands
is in the Spratlys.
It's the southern part of the
South China

23:31.043 --> 23:36.448 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Sea. And the Chinese rejected
this ruling
from the outset. They claimed
that the tribunal

23:36.482 --> 23:42.655 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
didn't have jurisdiction on any
of these issues.
So, the Chinese refused to
participate in

23:42.688 --> 23:48.394 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
