have claimed
that it is not binding on China.

23:48.427 --> 23:53.165 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, according to the Convention
on the Law
of the Sea -- and China is a
state party -- it

23:53.198 --> 23:56.935 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is binding on both parties, the
Philippines
and China.

23:56.969 --> 24:00.572 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, what does
it mean, then?
China, as you say, is rejecting
the ruling.

24:00.606 --> 24:04.777 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They're saying it's an invalid
-- was invalid
for the court to even consider
this. What

24:04.810 --> 24:08.113 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
does it mean, then? Is it
enforceable in any
way, this decision?

24:08.147 --> 24:14.253 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BONNIE GLASER: There is no
enforcement mechanism,
Judy, under the Convention on
the Law of the

24:14.286 --> 24:22.728 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Sea. And so it's really left up
to the international
community to encourage China to
be a law-abiding

24:22.761 --> 24:28.434 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
citizen and for China to see
that it's in
its interest to not be an
outlaw.

24:28.467 --> 24:32.971 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
China wants to, I believe, rise
peacefully.
It doesn't want to have
confrontation with

24:33.005 --> 24:39.511 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
its neighbors. So I think this
is going to
create some thinking, maybe
rethinking in

24:39.545 --> 24:44.483 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
China about its approach top its
neighbors,
I hope. But in the short run,
we're likely

24:44.516 --> 24:50.589 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to see increased tensions, and I
think that
the Chinese might take some
steps to reassert

24:50.622 --> 24:55.160 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
their claims, because Xi Jinping
will face
pressure domestically.

24:55.194 --> 25:02.401 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He has lost face on this issue,
because this
award, as they call it, the
decision, was

25:02.434 --> 25:07.005 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
almost completely in favor of
the Philippines.
It was very one-sided.

25:07.039 --> 25:12.878 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So you do see
China, perhaps,
rethinking its approach on this?
And, just

25:12.911 --> 25:18.350 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
quickly, effect on the United
States, which
clearly has a lot at stake with
its allies

25:18.384 --> 25:20.152 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in the Pacific?

25:20.185 --> 25:23.389 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BONNIE GLASER: Yes, well, the
United States
has made its interests quite
clear in the

25:23.422 --> 25:29.161 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Pacific. It wants to have a
rules-based order
and wants to see China part of
that rules-based

25:29.194 --> 25:30.863 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
order.

25:30.896 --> 25:34.199 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So we will have to see going
forward whether
this becomes a source of renewed
tensions

25:34.233 --> 25:38.971 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in the South China Sea between
China and its
neighbors and between the U.S.
and China,

25:39.004 --> 25:44.543 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
or whether we can put this issue
on a diplomatic
track and find ways for
bilateral fishing

25:44.576 --> 25:50.416 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
agreements, joint energy
exploration and other
ways, solve these disputes, and
find ways

25:50.449 --> 25:51.683 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to cooperate.

25:51.717 --> 25:53.786 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: A lot of
questions coming out
of this ruling.

25:53.819 --> 25:58.957 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Bonnie Glaser with CSIS, the
Center for Strategic
and International Studies, we
thank you.

25:58.991 --> 26:02.194 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
BONNIE GLASER: Thank you.

26:02.227 --> 26:12.704 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Tonight, we continue
our series
The end of AIDS.

26:12.738 --> 26:17.109 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Yesterday, we looked at San
Francisco and
at one of the nation's most
ambitious plans

26:17.142 --> 26:21.947 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to curtail AIDS. Tonight, we
turn to a city
where the struggle is much more
difficult.

26:21.980 --> 26:27.219 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Atlanta, Georgia, and much of
the Southeast
is, by some measures, the
epicenter of America's

26:27.252 --> 26:29.021 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
AIDS crisis.

26:29.054 --> 26:32.791 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, as correspondent William
Brangham and
producer Jason Kane report, the
barriers to

26:32.825 --> 26:35.861 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
stemming the epidemic there are
enormous.

26:35.894 --> 26:40.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This report was supported by the
Pulitzer
Center on Crisis Reporting.

26:40.499 --> 26:46.238 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: The alarm
bells rarely stop
in the inpatient and isolation
wards at Grady

26:46.271 --> 26:48.574 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Memorial Hospital.

26:48.607 --> 26:54.546 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Here in Atlanta, just down the
street from
the CDC, in 2016, in the age of
lifesaving

26:54.580 --> 26:59.585 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
antiretroviral drugs, hundreds
of people are
still dying every year from
AIDS.

26:59.618 --> 27:03.489 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. CARLOS DEL RIO, Emory Center
for AIDS
Research: The epidemic of HIV in
America is

27:03.522 --> 27:08.026 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
forgotten, but not gone. People
have forgotten
it exists. I think I have a
better chance

27:08.060 --> 27:11.964 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of winning the lottery than I
have of ending
AIDS in where we are today,
right?

27:11.997 --> 27:16.335 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: The
Southeastern U.S. is
the epicenter of America's
epidemic. These

27:16.368 --> 27:21.974 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
states make up 44 percent of
people living
with HIV, and they make up half
of all new

27:22.007 --> 27:23.775 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
HIV diagnoses.

27:23.809 --> 27:27.713 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. CARLOS DEL RIO: It's almost
like the South
is a different country. It
really is about

27:27.746 --> 27:33.385 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
poverty, the social determinants
of health,
racism. It's really a bunch of
different things.

27:33.418 --> 27:37.356 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Carlos Del Rio
is one of
Atlanta's leading HIV doctors.
He co-directs

27:37.389 --> 27:40.993 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the Emory Center for AIDS
Research, and sees
patients at Grady.

27:41.026 --> 27:46.231 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Often, he says, patients have no
idea of their
HIV status until it's nearly too
late.

27:46.265 --> 27:50.035 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. CARLOS DEL RIO: Half those
people we diagnose
here already have AIDS. In other
words, they

27:50.068 --> 27:52.571 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
have been infected for five,
six, 10 years.

27:52.604 --> 27:56.942 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Russell Martin
was one of
them. Black gay men are one of
the hardest-hit

27:56.975 --> 27:59.144 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
populations here in the
Southeast.

27:59.177 --> 28:03.081 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Martin thought he was perfectly
healthy, until
one day he came down with a
fever.

28:03.115 --> 28:08.520 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RUSSELL MARTIN, AIDS Patient:
I'm just thinking
it was a cold. I have asthma, so
I'm prone

28:08.554 --> 28:11.990 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to having pneumonia, so I'm
like, OK, maybe
it's just pneumonia.

28:12.024 --> 28:16.528 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: By the time he
checked into
Grady, he was so sick that
doctors induced

28:16.562 --> 28:21.900 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a near-coma in a desperate
attempt to save
him. He woke up to learn that he
had HIV,

28:21.934 --> 28:25.671 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
it had progressed to AIDS, and
that he had
nearly died.

28:25.704 --> 28:29.741 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's not that Martin didn't know
about HIV
or wasn't being careful. In
fact, he once

28:29.775 --> 28:32.844 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
worked at an HIV clinic and got
tested regularly.

28:32.878 --> 28:38.584 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RUSSELL MARTIN: I got routine
checks until
I got into a relationship. And
it was once

28:38.617 --> 28:40.385 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I was in a relationship, I
didn't do it.

28:40.419 --> 28:44.089 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Because you
thought, "I'm
in a monogamous relationship, I
don't need

28:44.122 --> 28:45.357 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to be tested."

28:45.390 --> 28:47.259 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RUSSELL MARTIN: That's true.
That's what I
was thinking.

28:47.292 --> 28:51.330 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: While Martin
is currently
on treatment and doing well,
he's become further

28:51.363 --> 28:54.032 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
evidence for an alarming
projection.

28:54.066 --> 28:58.604 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
According to a recent analysis
that was done
by the CDC here in Atlanta, if
current trends

28:58.637 --> 29:05.477 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
