bisexual black men
will be diagnosed with HIV in
their lifetimes,

29:05.510 --> 29:07.346 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
half.

29:07.379 --> 29:09.815 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Fulton County Commissioner Joan
Garner has
been helping lead the push to
change the course

29:09.848 --> 29:14.553 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of the epidemic here in Atlanta.
She started
after hearing that few cities in
the country

29:14.586 --> 29:16.388 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
have higher rates of HIV

29:16.421 --> 29:21.660 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOAN GARNER, Fulton County
Commissioner: The
information has been out there.
Research is

29:21.693 --> 29:28.667 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
out there. Treatments --
treatment is out
there. And I was just floored
when I heard

29:28.700 --> 29:31.003 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that, and I said, we have got to
do something
about this.

29:31.036 --> 29:33.138 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN EAVES, Fulton County
Chairman: We certainly
have some new leadership.

29:33.171 --> 29:37.442 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Two years ago,
Garner and
council Chair John Eaves
assembled the Fulton

29:37.476 --> 29:42.681 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
County Task Force on HIV/AIDS.
Fulton County
makes up the bulk of the city of
Atlanta.

29:42.714 --> 29:48.286 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOMAN: This really shouldn't be
a conversation
anymore. This is low-hanging
fruit. We swing

29:48.320 --> 29:50.188 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the gate literally from one end
to the other.

29:50.222 --> 29:53.759 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Like San
Francisco, which
we reported on earlier, they are
one of the

29:53.792 --> 29:59.231 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
first local governments in the
U.S. to formalize
a plan for ending AIDS. The
exact budget and

29:59.264 --> 30:01.066 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
timeline of their work is yet to
be determined.

30:01.099 --> 30:03.001 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. MELANIE THOMPSON, Fulton
County Task Force
on HIV/AIDS: There are a lot of
people who

30:03.035 --> 30:05.671 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
are working on this, not
necessarily working
together.

30:05.704 --> 30:09.508 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Dr. Melanie
Thompson is
helping lead the task force. She
says it's

30:09.541 --> 30:13.078 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
unbelievable to her that it's
taken this long
to get started.

30:13.111 --> 30:17.482 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. MELANIE THOMPSON: It's
horrifying. I mean,
frankly, we have had a
smoldering epidemic

30:17.516 --> 30:25.691 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
here for a long time. But when
