bit of political will, it goes a
long way,

30:25.724 --> 30:27.959 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and that is something that we
have never had
here.

30:27.993 --> 30:31.363 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: But the
challenges are daunting,
something the task force has
been hearing

30:31.396 --> 30:36.001 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
about as they have traveled
across the county,
meeting with various groups,
from gay, bisexual

30:36.034 --> 30:40.439 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and transgender organizations to
those who
inject drugs.

30:40.472 --> 30:45.043 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's estimated there are 3,000
HIV-positive
people in the county who don't
know they're

30:45.077 --> 30:48.547 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
infected, meaning they could
unknowingly be
spreading the virus to others.

30:48.580 --> 30:53.285 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. MELANIE THOMPSON: At a time
when San Francisco
is talking about getting to
zero, and New

30:53.318 --> 31:00.592 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
York is talking about ending the
epidemic,
we still see increasing numbers
of new HIV

31:00.625 --> 31:03.395 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
diagnoses in some of our
population.

31:03.428 --> 31:09.501 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: For those who
do know their
status, and want to start
treatment, just

31:09.534 --> 31:11.570 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
getting there can be arduous.

31:11.603 --> 31:16.007 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Claude Bowen's difficult commute
to the doctor
isn't uncommon in this sprawling
city. He

31:16.041 --> 31:18.877 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
has no car and has to travel two
hours to
his appointments.

31:18.910 --> 31:24.916 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CLAUDE BOWEN, AIDS Patient: I
take one bus
to the train to another bus. If
I come down

31:24.950 --> 31:30.122 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
here, I take a bus, the train,
another train,
then a bus.

31:30.155 --> 31:31.590 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: And that's
just one way?

31:31.623 --> 31:33.592 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
CLAUDE BOWEN: That's one way.

31:33.625 --> 31:36.862 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: If a bus or
train is late,
he will miss the next leg, and
often his appointment

31:36.895 --> 31:41.633 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
will be canceled entirely. For
these reasons
and many others, an estimated 40
percent to

31:41.666 --> 31:47.973 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
50 percent of people in Fulton
County drop
out of HIV care once they have
started. For

31:48.006 --> 31:51.042 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
others, even basic information
about treatment
can be a struggle.

31:51.076 --> 31:52.844 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DERRICK LANGFORD, AIDS Patient:
I'm going
for like this Bohemian-type
thing.

31:52.878 --> 31:56.882 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: When
22-year-old Derrick
Langford was diagnosed with HIV,
he had no

31:56.915 --> 32:00.852 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
trouble opening up to friends
and family.

32:00.886 --> 32:05.924 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But he couldn't figure out what
to do next
or where to go for medication or
follow-up

32:05.957 --> 32:07.626 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
care.

32:07.659 --> 32:11.797 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DERRICK LANGFORD: So, it was
pretty much me
searching, looking, using Google
a lot to

32:11.830 --> 32:18.737 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
find out where I needed to go.
And the stress
kind of made me very, very sick.

32:18.770 --> 32:23.008 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: It's often
these kinds of
barriers, not riskier behaviors,
that drive

32:23.041 --> 32:27.913 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
these high rates of infection.
In fact, gay
black men don't engage in
higher-risk behaviors

32:27.946 --> 32:31.683 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
compared to, say, white gay men.
Repeated
studies have proven that.

32:31.716 --> 32:36.288 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They often have fewer partners
and use condoms
more, says Wendy Armstrong.
She's medical

32:36.321 --> 32:41.626 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
director of the Ponce De Leon
Center, Grady
Hospital's massive outpatient
clinic for Atlanta's

32:41.660 --> 32:43.562 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
HIV-positive community.

32:43.595 --> 32:46.398 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. WENDY ARMSTRONG, Ponce De
Leon Center:
There's so much easy blame:
Those people shouldn't

32:46.431 --> 32:50.969 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
be doing those things. And that
is not the
situation at all. It is that it
is such a

32:51.002 --> 32:55.941 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
