Homs is in a mess and chaos,
killing, stealing.

43:38.616 --> 43:44.322 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
People are dying. We closed our
shops. Every
day, two or three or four get
kidnapped. Shame

43:44.355 --> 43:47.925 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on them. We want to finish this.
This is not
a solution.

43:47.959 --> 43:52.730 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Despite the
indiscriminate
shelling of the city, Colvin's
younger sister,

43:52.763 --> 43:55.500 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Cathleen, says that Marie's
death was no accident.

43:55.533 --> 43:58.569 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CATHLEEN COLVIN, Sister of Marie
Colvin: I
was absolutely sure from the
very beginning

43:58.603 --> 44:05.476 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that she was targeted. The
timing of her last
report out of Homs was -- seemed
like too

44:05.510 --> 44:07.411 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
much of a coincidence.

44:07.445 --> 44:10.448 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: That last
report was a series
of phone interviews Colvin did
with American

44:10.481 --> 44:15.453 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and British TV networks. In
them, she described
the Assad government's attack on
civilians

44:15.486 --> 44:16.687 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
in Homs.

44:16.721 --> 44:18.823 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
This one was with the U.K.'s
Channel 4 News.

44:18.856 --> 44:22.660 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARIE COLVIN, Journalist: I am
at ground zero,
and I am seeing what's being
hit. Civilian

44:22.693 --> 44:27.765 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
